$templateCache.put("component/faq/faq.html","<h2 translate>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\n\n<ul class=\"faq\">\n    <li>\n        <h4 translate>How can I help?</h4>\n        <p translate>GGG is the lovechild of a couple hardcore Destiny fans. If you like what we\'ve done and want to show your\n        support, feel free to buy us a beer and/or pony!</p>\n\n        <form action=\"https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr\" method=\"post\" target=\"_top\">\n            <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"cmd\" value=\"_s-xclick\">\n            <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"hosted_button_id\" value=\"L5SUDPCS8DNSN\">\n            <input type=\"image\" src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/btn/btn_donate_SM.gif\" border=\"0\" name=\"submit\" alt=\"PayPal - The safer, easier way to pay online!\">\n            <img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/scr/pixel.gif\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\">\n        </form>\n\n        <br />\n\n        <p translate>More technical users are invited to contribute on our\n            <a href=\"https://github.com/guardiangg/http-client\">GitHub repository</a>, we\'re open source!\n        </p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <h4 translate>How accurate is this data?</h4>\n        <p translate>\n            Since the launch of the Taken King, we have aggregated data from every single match played. Our rankings\n            are updated in real-time and immediately available. If you have played Destiny recently, particularly in the\n            Crucible, you have a profile here - check it out!\n        </p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <h4 translate>What is \"Elo\" and what does it mean?</h4>\n        <p>\n            <translate translate-comment=\"Used in the line: From Wikipedia:\">From</translate>\n            <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system\">Wikipedia</a>:\n        </p>\n        <blockquote translate>\n            The Elo rating system is a method for calculating the relative skill levels of players in\n            competitor-versus-competitor games.\n        </blockquote>\n        <p translate>\n            All players start at a baseline of 1200 points. You will take points from your opponent\'s Elo score by\n            defeating them, and vise versa. Defeating a more skilled opponent will yield higher points than if you beat up\n            on a weaker one. The higher the score, the more skilled the player. It is extremely difficult\n            to maintain a high Elo score, these players are regarded as the best of the best!\n        </p>\n\n        <p translate>\n            As your score rises and falls, you\'ll be categorized into leagues.\n        </p>\n\n        <ul>\n            <li><translate>Bronze</translate>: 0-1099</li>\n            <li><translate>Silver</translate>: 1100-1299</li>\n            <li><translate>Gold</translate>: 1300-1499</li>\n            <li><translate>Platinum</translate>: 1500-1699</li>\n            <li><translate>Diamond</translate>: 1700+</li>\n        </ul>\n\n        <p translate>\n            Each mode you play has its own Elo rating and league categorization. Beyond that, Elo is account-wide, so in\n            Control you\'ll have the same rating whether you\'re on your Titan, Warlock or Hunter.\n        </p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <h4 translate>How do I get in touch if I have a question/suggestion?</h4>\n        <p>\n            <translate>You can fire us an email at</translate> <a href=\"mailto:guardiandotgg@gmail.com\">guardiandotgg@gmail.com</a>\n        </p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n");
